soot.jimple.toolkits.annotation.purity

Class DirectedCallGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.toolkits.annotation.purity.DirectedCallGraph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<SootMethod>, DirectedGraph<SootMethod>

    public class DirectedCallGraph
extends Object
implements DirectedGraph<SootMethod>
    Builds a DirectedGraph from a CallGraph and SootMethodFilter. This is used in AbstractInterproceduralAnalysis to construct a reverse pseudo topological order on which to iterate. You can specify a SootMethodFilter to trim the graph by cutting call edges. Methods filtered-out by the SootMethodFilter will not appear in the DirectedGraph!

      • DirectedCallGraph

        public DirectedCallGraph(CallGraph cg,
                         SootMethodFilter filter,
                         Iterator<SootMethod> heads,
                         boolean verbose)
        The constructor does all the work here. After constructed, you can safely use all interface methods. Moreover, these methods should perform very fast... The DirectedGraph will only contain methods in call paths from a method in head and comprising only methods wanted by filter. Moreover, only concrete methods are put in the graph...
